# Use one-true-brace-style. Linux braces with braced single-statement blocks
--style=1tbs
# Attach braces to single-statement blocks (e.g. if/else)
-j
# Convert tabs to spaces
-c
# Indent C++ style // comments
-Y
# Pad around if/else blocks
-f
# Pad header if( -> if (
-H
# Attach pointer to type. char *x -> char* x
-k1

# Indent with 4 spaces
-s4

# Indent switch 'case:' headers
-S
